{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1478141b-65cd-4bee-ba7f-3c843a8c7932","content":"The workspace is empty, so there's no existing file to convert. Let me explain the conversion and provide the code directly.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\nAdd `x:DataType` to your `ContentPage` element, pointing at your ViewModel type. This enables compile-time validation of all `{Binding}` expressions on that page.\n\n**Before (interpreted bindings):**\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             x:Class=\"MyApp.Views.SettingsPage\">\n    <StackLayout>\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize}\" />\n    </StackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\n**After (compiled bindings):**\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:MyApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"MyApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n    <StackLayout>\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='{0}'}\" />\n    </StackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nKey changes:\n1. **`xmlns:vm`** — imports the ViewModel's namespace.\n2. **`x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"`** — tells the XAML compiler the type of the `BindingContext`, enabling compile-time checks for every `{Binding}` on the page.\n\n## Catching Binding Errors at Build Time\n\nOnce `x:DataType` is set, the compiler validates property names and types. To ensure errors surface as **build failures** (not just warnings), add this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <WarningsAsErrors>$(WarningsAsErrors);XC0045</WarningsAsErrors>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n`XC0045` is the XAML compiler warning for binding path issues. Promoting it to an error means a typo like `{Binding Thme}` will **break the build** instead of silently failing at runtime.\n\n### Tips\n- You can scope `x:DataType` to any element, not just the page root — useful for `DataTemplate` inside a `CollectionView`.\n- To opt out for a specific binding (e.g., a relative or ancestor binding), use `x:DataType=\"\"` locally to disable compiled bindings on that subtree.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"96a85b11-4a16-40b8-bdae-80b03dd91695","outputTokens":689,"requestId":"F3DF:C1158:1EE2E0D:22AC452:69E81991"},"id":"fad12920-4a13-418d-98f5-9979bb224298","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:43:11.406Z","parentId":"861134f6-33d7-4686-aec8-ba55fa65c780"}
